# SrujanaSangama Global Gitignore

# 1. Block all live user memory and context files inside plugins
# Allows committed example templates (*.md.example) but blocks live user profiles
plugins/*/memory/**/*.md
!plugins/*/memory/**/*.md.example
plugins/*/memory/*.md
!plugins/*/memory/*.md.example

# Allows committed example templates (*.md.example) but blocks live user contexts
plugins/*/context/**/*.md
!plugins/*/context/**/*.md.example
plugins/*/context/*.md
!plugins/*/context/*.md.example

# Explicitly ignore common live memory and context filenames
soul.md
tasks.md
wellbeing-log.md
ikigai.md
active-project.md
current-session.md
scratchpad.md
scholar-profile.md
research-tracker.md
publication-pipeline.md
daily-log.md

# 2. Block evaluation logs and transient test outputs
eval/logs/*.log
eval/scratch/

# 3. Standard developer environments
.vscode/
node_modules/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# 4. Centralized User Memory Folder
memory/

# 5. Operational mode file — gitignored (production is default when absent)
# The committed template is context/mode.md.example
context/mode.md
